Requirements:

Design goals:
- 0-24V @ 4A
- Two isolated channels
- Dedicated 2A USB socket
- Fixed 5V, 3.3V outputs
- Keypad numemrical input for I & V (PCB-mounted cherry MX switches?)
- Dual encoder wheels (one to set voltage, one to set current)
- Separate output enable/disable switches for each output, with LED indicator when on
- CC mode status LED
- Driven by STM32F4 ARM MCU
- H/W for a USB serial/LAN interface
- backlit LCD display with set + actual voltage/current